24/02/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The new Chief of Police, Dan Fatuloiu, said at a news conference Wednesday (23 February) that managers are working to ensure reforms recommended by the EU are fulfilled.
Fatuloiu, appointed to the post at the beginning of February, said an action plan for tackling seven concrete areas has been drafted.
Also Wednesday, the Association of Romanian Exporters and Importers called for the governor of the National Bank to resign over the rise of the leu.
The Romanian currency has gone up by more than nine percentage points against the euro and the US dollar in less than two months.
(Nine o'clock, AP - 23/02/05)
